    }\n  ]\n}"}},"metadata":{},"execution_count":35}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["🛍️💻 After collecting and cleaning a dataset of over 1,000 products listed on Amazon, we developed a recommendation system using machine learning algorithms to suggest products to users based on their interests and previous purchases. 🧐👨‍💻\n","\n","Now, let's take a look at some insights that can be extracted from our system and how they can be valuable for a company:\n","\n","👉 Understanding customer preferences: By analyzing the products that each user has purchased, we can identify which categories and features are more attractive to them. This information can be used to optimize product design and marketing strategies to better target specific groups of customers.\n","\n","👉 Increasing customer engagement: By suggesting relevant products to users based on their interests, we can increase their engagement with the platform and their satisfaction with the shopping experience. This can lead to higher customer retention and loyalty.\n","\n","👉 Improving sales: By recommending products that are similar or complementary to the ones that users have already purchased, we can increase the chances of cross-selling and up-selling. This can result in higher revenue and profit for the company.\n","\n","Overall, our Simple Recommendation System provides a powerful tool for companies to better understand their customers, improve their engagement and satisfaction, and increase their sales. 💡\n","\n","Thank you for checking out our project! Stay tuned for more insights and recommendations in the future. 😊👍\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"sp9RwmX1a0-3"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["####"],"metadata":{"id":"ekAcVC3Q0vKZ"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Model-Flow"],"metadata":{"id":"d9BhQ2tn1FIQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["####"],"metadata":{"id":"00YaxHp60_RR"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"d9069ec4"},"source":["## Save Recommendation System Components to Drive\n","\n","Now that the TF-IDF vectorizer is fitted and the DataFrame is processed, we can save these components to Google Drive for later reuse. This avoids the need to re-process data every time we want to make recommendations.\n","\n","We will save:\n","- The `tfidf_vectorizer` object using `pickle`.\n","- The processed `df` DataFrame using `parquet` for efficient storage."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"f6e8fce5","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1779981933354,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":78,"user":{"displayName":"practice session","userId":"06899126492144380653"}},"outputId":"1b426290-bdcd-4ea6-8c43-4a97c4320d2b"},"source":["import pickle\n","import os\n","\n","# Define your Google Drive folder ID\n","folder_id = '1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv' # User-provided folder ID\n","\n","# Define paths in Google Drive\n","save_path = f'/content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_{folder_id}'\n","\n","# Create the directory if it doesn't exist\n","os.makedirs(save_path, exist_ok=True)\n","\n","# Save the TF-IDF vectorizer\n","tfidf_vectorizer_filename = os.path.join(save_path, 'tfidf_vectorizer.pkl')\n","with open(tfidf_vectorizer_filename, 'wb') as f:\n","    pickle.dump(tfidf_vectorizer, f)\n","print(f\"TF-IDF vectorizer saved to: {tfidf_vectorizer_filename}\")\n","\n","# Save the processed DataFrame\n","df_filename = os.path.join(save_path, 'processed_df.parquet')\n","df.to_parquet(df_filename, index=False)\n","print(f\"Processed DataFrame saved to: {df_filename}\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["TF-IDF vectorizer saved to: /content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv/tfidf_vectorizer.pkl\n","Processed DataFrame saved to: /content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv/processed_df.parquet\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"a04c484c"},"source":["## Load Recommendation System Components from Drive\n","\n","To demonstrate reuse, we will now load the saved TF-IDF vectorizer and the processed DataFrame from Google Drive. This simulates loading previously saved components without re-running the data preparation and TF-IDF fitting steps."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7ca81fd4","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1779981934127,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":768,"user":{"displayName":"practice session","userId":"06899126492144380653"}},"outputId":"9ddf31f7-f7b0-47f8-fcc9-1cd3ae71acb0"},"source":["import pickle\n","import pandas as pd\n","import os\n","\n","# Define your Google Drive folder ID (same as used for saving)\n","folder_id = '1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv'\n","\n","# Define paths in Google Drive\n","load_path = f'/content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_{folder_id}'\n","\n","# Load the TF-IDF vectorizer\n","loaded_tfidf_vectorizer_filename = os.path.join(load_path, 'tfidf_vectorizer.pkl')\n","with open(loaded_tfidf_vectorizer_filename, 'rb') as f:\n","    loaded_tfidf_vectorizer = pickle.load(f)\n","print(f\"TF-IDF vectorizer loaded from: {loaded_tfidf_vectorizer_filename}\")\n","\n","# Load the processed DataFrame\n","loaded_df_filename = os.path.join(load_path, 'processed_df.parquet')\n","loaded_df = pd.read_parquet(loaded_df_filename)\n","print(f\"Processed DataFrame loaded from: {loaded_df_filename}\")\n","\n","# Re-compute TF-IDF matrix using the loaded vectorizer and loaded_df\n","# This is necessary because the matrix itself wasn't saved, only the vectorizer.\n","loaded_tfidf_matrix = loaded_tfidf_vectorizer.transform(loaded_df['about_product'])\n","print(\"TF-IDF matrix re-computed using loaded vectorizer and DataFrame.\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["TF-IDF vectorizer loaded from: /content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv/tfidf_vectorizer.pkl\n","Processed DataFrame loaded from: /content/gdrive/MyDrive/Colab Notebooks/RecommendationSystem_saved_components_1MKXxTjXqbhMKu7tKTjZwkTbZezj3Brxv/processed_df.parquet\n","TF-IDF matrix re-computed using loaded vectorizer and DataFrame.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{"id":"71e661b1"},"source":["## Integrate Loaded Components for Recommendations\n","\n","Now we can use the `loaded_tfidf_vectorizer`, `loaded_tfidf_matrix`, and `loaded_df` to make recommendations, demonstrating that the saved components can be effectively reused."]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":224},"id":"c0ae1166","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1779981934201,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":63,"user":{"displayName":"practice session","userId":"06899126492144380653"}},"outputId":"3b055f61-09d2-40c7-a506-75a7803ad14c"},"source":["from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n","\n","def recommend_products_from_loaded(df, tfidf_vectorizer, tfidf_matrix, user_id_encoded):\n","    # Get the purchase history for the user from the loaded DataFrame\n","    user_history = df[df['user_id_encoded'] == user_id_encoded]\n","\n","    # Get the indices of the products purchased by the user\n","    indices = user_history.index.tolist()\n","\n","    if indices:\n","        # Calculate cosine similarity between the user's purchased products and all other products\n","        # using the loaded TF-IDF matrix\n","        cosine_sim_user = cosine_similarity(tfidf_matrix[indices], tfidf_matrix)\n","\n","        # Create a pandas Series with product indices as the index and product names as the values\n","        products = df.iloc[indices]['product_name']\n","        product_indices_series = pd.Series(products.index, index=products)\n","\n","        # Get similarity scores, excluding products already purchased by the user\n","        similarity_scores = list(enumerate(cosine_sim_user[-1]))\n","        similarity_scores = [(i, score) for (i, score) in similarity_scores if i not in product_indices_series]\n","\n","        # Sort the similarity scores in descending order\n","        similarity_scores = sorted(similarity_scores, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n","\n","        # Get the indices of the top 5 most similar products\n","        top_products = [i[0] for i in similarity_scores[1:6]]\n","\n","        # Get the names of the top 5 most similar products from the loaded DataFrame\n","        recommended_products = df.iloc[top_products]['product_name'].tolist()\n","\n","        # Get the reasons (similarity scores) for the recommendation\n","        score = [similarity_scores[i][1] for i in range(5)]\n","\n","        # Create a DataFrame with the results\n","        results_df = pd.DataFrame({'Id Encoded': [user_id_encoded] * 5,\n","                                   'recommended product': recommended_products,\n","                                   'score recommendation': score})\n","\n","        return results_df\n","\n","    else:\n","        print(\"No purchase history found for this user in the loaded data.\")\n","        return None\n","\n","# Demonstrate using the loaded components\n","# Assuming id_example is still available from previous execution or re-run\n","# If not, you might need to re-encode a user_id from loaded_df\n","# For demonstration, let's pick a user_id_encoded from loaded_df\n","demo_user_id = loaded_df['user_id_encoded'].sample(1).iloc[0]\n","print(f\"Making recommendations for user_id_encoded: {demo_user_id}\")\n","\n","recommendations = recommend_products_from_loaded(loaded_df, loaded_tfidf_vectorizer, loaded_tfidf_matrix, demo_user_id)\n","display(recommendations)"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Making recommendatio